race.comment: ORAQUA (9) was quickly back on track when narrowly beaten in an 80 at Flemington. He came from back, stepping up to this trip, and there was plenty of merit in the effort. She's on the improve and has the tongue tie on for the first time. EARLY WARNING (7) was finally back to his best beaten 1L in stronger at Ararat. Has Linda and a low gate and she will go close holding that form. PROMISED LAND (1) has been knocking on the door and has jumped out well when last seen 28 days ago. The 3kg claim brings him right into it. COUSINS DAY (13) goes in at a price. The step up in trip suits and he tumbles in weight. Winning rider Yendall is reunited, and she's got plenty of scope for improvement.
